      "text": "Writing The Boy in the Iceberg, Pu-on Tim spent weeks at a time on the road, stayed up for days, researched leads, and followed the Avatar. He often described the experience of following the Avatar as a \"painful and blurry dream\", something that nearly drove him insane. However, his work resulted in him having hundreds of scrolls filled with notes about the Avatar, and he could not have been happier with his unbiased view of the Avatar and his companions. He called The Boy in the Iceberg his \"masterpiece\", though other critics were less kind about the play, calling it merely \"watchable\"."
